. The rules suggest avoiding direct reflection unless it’s part of a public API, but with a dynamic class being package-private, I might be stuck using reflection. I wonder if MethodHandles could work for me, but that also counts as reflection. I might need to patch the module in my build.gradle to add the library jar path. I'm not sure about accessing the resolveTestedLibraryJars closure—maybe it needs to come after the plugin in my setup?\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_uwhsuepvPTdRfrOquYrfvuk3|fc_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cfd04f508190829cb3007615e71c\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"patch-module|--add-opens|jvmArgs|runtimeArgs\\\" tests/src -n | head -100\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 27842, \"output\": 1330, \"cacheRead\": 7168, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 36340, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777913786964, \"responseId\": \"resp_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cfbbe7a8819082a3098c980a5d1f\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_uwhsuepvPTdRfrOquYrfvuk3|fc_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cfd04f508190829cb3007615e71c\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/src/org.apache-extras.beanshell/bsh/2.0b6/build.gradle:21:            runtimeArgs(\\\"-Djava.home=${System.getenv('JAVA_HOME')}\\\")\\ntests/src/org.apache-extras.beanshell/bsh/2.0b6/build.gradle:22:            runtimeArgs(\\\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\\\")\\ntests/src/AGENTS.md:5:- The model may modify `buildArgs` in `build.gradle` only in `graalvmNative` and only to add `--add-opens` or `--add-exports arguments`.\\ntests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build.gradle:56:        jvmArgs \\\"-Xbootclasspath/a:${bootClasspath}\\\",\\ntests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-config